More than 100 farmers were yesterday locked out of the Kimalel Goat Auction in Baringo county for arriving late. They had more than 600 goats.A total of 2,326 goats were sold during the international auction presided over by Deputy President William Ruto.Every goat was sold at Sh12,000. Ruto concluded the exercise within less than 15 minutes. A total of Sh28,242 was raised.Ruto and President Uhuru Kenyatta paid Sh7.4 million in cash for 616 goats, while Egeyo Marakwet Senator Kipchumba Murkomen paid Sh1.2 million cash for 100 goats, same to Water PS Fred Segor and businessman Joshua Kulei.Other leaders who bought the goats in cash were Baringo Governor Benjamin Cheboi (100), Baringo Central MP Sammy Mwaita (20), woman representative Grace Kiptui (10) and Tiaty MP Asman Kamama (50).